<Paragraph FontWeight="Bold" FontFamily="Cambria" FontSize="16">
Features
</Paragraph>

<List Margin="25,0,0,0">
<ListItem><Paragraph>Chart legends can be set to any location relative to a chart such as the bottom, top, left, right, or they can be floated.</Paragraph></ListItem>
<ListItem><Paragraph>The chart legend's border color can be changed.</Paragraph></ListItem>
<ListItem><Paragraph>Legend icons with check boxes can be displayed.</Paragraph></ListItem>
</List>


<Paragraph FontWeight="Bold" FontFamily="Cambria" FontSize="16">
Interactive Features</Paragraph>

<List Margin="25,0,0,0">



<ListItem>
<Paragraph>To show icons in a legend, select the <Bold>"Show Icons in Legend"</Bold> combo box.</Paragraph>
</ListItem>

<ListItem>
<Paragraph>To show/hide legend, select the <Bold>"Visibility Of Legend"</Bold> combo box.</Paragraph>
</ListItem>



<ListItem>
<Paragraph>The template of a legend icon can be changed by modifying values in the <Bold>"Template"</Bold> combo box.</Paragraph>
</ListItem>

<ListItem>
<Paragraph>To set the border brush of a legend, select a value from the <Bold>"Select Border Brush"</Bold> combo box.</Paragraph>
</ListItem>

<ListItem>
<Paragraph>To dock a legend to the left, right, top, or bottom, select the appropriate value from the <Bold>"Select Legend Positions"</Bold> list box.</Paragraph>
</ListItem>

<ListItem>
<Paragraph>To move the legend to any X ,Y position, move  the <Bold>"DockX and DockY"</Bold> slider.</Paragraph>
</ListItem>


</List>


</FlowDocument>